ers of video games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One]]\n[[Category:Subscription services]]\n", "name_user": "Longdongwong", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRelease and reception", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EA_Access"}
{"title_page": "Betty Award", "text_new": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = Betty Award\n| current_awards = 22nd Betty Awards\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| description    = Outstanding achievement in [[Calgary]]'s professional [[theatre]] community\n| presenter      = \n| country        = {{CAN}}\n| year           = {{Start date and age|1998}}\n| website        = {{URL|bettymitchellawards.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Betty Mitchell Awards''' were created in 1998 to celebrate and honor outstanding achievement in Calgary's professional theatre community. It is commonly called the Betty Award and is named for Calgary theatre pioneer Dr. [[Betty Mitchell (theatre director)|Betty Mitchell]].<ref>{{Citation\n | last = Northof | first = Anne\n | author1-link =\n | title = Betty Mitchell\n | publisher = The Canadian Theatre Encyclopedia, [[Athabasca University Press]]\n | date = February 18, 2018\n | url = http://www.canadiantheatre.com/dict.pl?term=Mitchell%2C%20Betty\n | access-date = June 16, 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation\n | last = Morrow\n | first = Martin\n | title = City theatre launches Betty Mitchell Awards\n | newspaper = [[Calgary Herald]]\n | pages = E2\n | date = 18 June 1998\n | url = https://www.newspapers.com/image/485661225/?terms=%22betty%2Bmitchell%2Baward%22\n | archive-url =\n | archive-date =\n | access-date = 15 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Citation\n | last = Brooks\n | first = Bill\n | title = Betty Mitchell Awards honor the best of city's theatre world\n | newspaper = [[Calgary Herald]]\n | pages = \n | date = 4 September 2014\n | url = http://www.calgaryherald.com/entertainment/Betty+Mitchell+Awards+honour+best+city+theatre+world/10177957/story.html\n | archive-url =\n | archive-date =\n | access-date = 15 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nThe awards ceremony for the 2018\u201319 season was held on June 24 at the Vertigo Theatre in Calgary.<ref>Louis B. Hobson, [https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/theatre/schemers-and-spies-top-the-betty-mitchell-award-nominations Schemers and spies top the Betty Mitchell Award nominations], [[Calgary Herald]], June 5, 2019</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Pakistani-Canadian actor [[Ahad Raza Mir]], the first [[Pakistani]] actor to play [[Hamlet]] in [[Canada]],<ref>News Desk, [https://dailytimes.com.pk/371438/ahad-raza-mir-becomes-first-pakistani-to-star-as-hamlet-in-canada/ Ahad Raza Mir becomes first Pakistani to star as Hamlet in Canada], [[Daily Times (Pakistan)]], March 31, 2019</ref> won the Betty for Outstanding Performance by an Actor in a Drama for his performance of the title role<ref>[https://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1158042 Ahad Raza Mir Wins the Betty Mitchell Award for Hamlet!], Hip In Pakistan</ref>  In that same year [[Tiffany Ayalik]] became the first [[Inuit]] recipient of a Betty Award.<ref>{{cite web |title=Inuit actress wins 'Outstanding Performance' prize |url=https://windspeaker.com/news/windspeaker-news/inuit-actress-wins-outstanding-performance-prize |website=[[Windspeaker]] |archivedate=August 25, 2019 |date=June 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Categories===\nAwards are given in the following categories:\n\n*Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble\n*Outstanding Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role\n*Outstanding Lighting Design\n*Outstanding Set Design\n*Outstanding Performance by an Actor in a Supporting Role\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|+ style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{nowrap|\u2022Outstanding Projection or Video Design}}\n|- style=\"background:#bebebe;\"! scope=\"col\" | Year! scope=\"col\" | Designer! scope=\"col\" | Production\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\"| 2019<ref name=\"2019nom\">Louis B. Hobson, [https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/theatre/betty-mitchell-theatre-awards-go-crazy-for-theatre-calgary Schemers and spies top the Betty Mitchell Award nominations], [[Calgary Herald]], June 5, 2019</ref>\n|- \n| Nicolas Dotsie\n| '''''BOOM X'''''\n|-\n| Bretta Gerecke\n|''The Invisible Agents of Ungentlemanly Warfare''\n|-\n| Amelia Scott\n| ''A Love Letter to Emily C''\n|-\n| Andy Moro   \n| ''Honour Beat''\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| '''[[Elaine J. McCarthy]]'''\n|'''''[[Everest (opera)|Everest]]'''''\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\"| 2018<ref name=\"2018win\">Louis B. Hobson, [https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/theatre/betty-mitchell-theatre-awards-go-crazy-for-theatre-calgary Puppets and sisters big winners at Betty Mitchell Awards], [[Calgary Herald]], June 26, 2018</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| '''Jamie Nesbitt'''\n| '''''Nine Dragons'''''\n|-\n| Remy Siu\n| ''Empire of the Son''\n|-\n| T. Erin Gruber\n| ''Easter Island''\n|-\n| Corwin Ferguson\n| ''[[Julius Caesar (play)|Julius Caesar]]''\n|-\n| Amelia Scott\n|''To the Light''\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\"| 2017<ref name=\"2017win\">Louis B. Hobson, [https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/theatre/betty-mitchell-theatre-awards-go-crazy-for-theatre-calgary Betty Mitchell Theatre Awards go Crazy for Theatre Calgary], [[Calgary Herald]], August 22, 2017</ref>\n|-\n| Corwin Ferguson\n| ''[[Richard III (play)|Richard III]]''\n|-\n| David Leclerc\n| ''BOOM''\n|-\n| Jamie Nesbitt\n| ''The Big Sleep''\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| '''Amelia Scott with illustrations by Tyler Jenkins'''\n| '''Crime Does Not Pay'''\n|-\n| JP Thibodeau\n|''Lest We Forget''\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\"| 2016<ref name=\"2016win\">Louis B. Hobson, [https://calgaryherald.com/entertainment/theatre/best-of-calgary-theatre-honoured-at-betty-mitchell-awards Best of Calgary theatre honoured at Betty Mitchell Awards], [[Calgary Herald]], August 23, 2016</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| '''Jamie Nesbitt'''\n| '''[[Calamity_Town#Adaptations|Calamity Town]]'''\n|-\n| Sean Nieuwenhuis\n| ''[[List_of_The_Little_Prince_adaptations#Operas_and_musical_productions|The Little Prince]]''\n|-\n| Scott Reid\n| ''[[Die Tote Stadt]]''\n|-\n| JP Thibodeau\n| ''The Boy\u2019s Own Jedi Handbook''\n|-\n| Amelia Scott and Joel Adria\n|''Cockroach''\n