s category|Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050630075920/http://www.isidore-of-seville.com/cortes/ Hernando Cortes on the Web]&nbsp;\u2013 web directory with thumbnail galleries\n* [http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/04397a.htm Catholic Encyclopedia] (1911)\n* [https://www.pbs.org/conquistadors/cortes/cortes_flat.html Conquistadors, with Michael Wood]&nbsp;\u2013 website for 2001 PBS documentary\n* [http://digital.library.wisc.edu/1711.dl/IbrAmerTxt Ibero-American Electronic Text Series] presented online by the [http://uwdc.library.wisc.edu/ University of Wisconsin Digital Collections Center]\n* [http://www.motecuhzoma.de/start-es.html P\u00e1gina de relaci\u00f3n]\n\n{{Spanish Empire}}\n{{coord|19.435|N|99.131|W|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tenochtitlan 1521}}\n[[Category:1521 in Mexico]]\n[[Category:1521 in New Spain]]\n[[Category:Battles involving canoes]]\n[[Category:Battles involving Spain]]\n[[Category:Battles involving Tlaxcala]]\n[[Category:Battles involving the Aztec Empire]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1521]]\n[[Category:Ethnic cleansing in North America]]\n[[Category:Genocide of indigenous peoples of the Americas]]\n[[Category:History of the Aztecs]]\n[[Category:Massacres of Native Americans]]\n[[Category:Native American genocide]]\n[[Category:Sieges involving Spain]]\n[[Category:Spanish conquests in the Americas]]\n[[Category:Tenochtitlan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military conflict\n|conflict=Fall of Tenochtitlan\n|partof=the [[Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire]]\n|image=The Conquest of Tenochtitlan.jpg\n|image_size=300px\n|caption=\"Conquista de M\u00e9xico por Cort\u00e9s\". Unknown artist, second half of the 17th century. Library of Congress, Washington, DC.\n|date=May 26 \u2013 August 13, 1521 Julian Date (2 months, 2 weeks and 4 days)\n|place=[[Tenochtitlan]], present-day [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]\n|result=Decisive Spanish and Tlaxcallan victory\n* Fall of the [[Aztec Empire]]\n|combatant